  "texts": [
    "Compared to simple graphs, standards-based hybrid graphs facilitate integration with other resources 31 and are more amenable to automated inference.",
    "They also provide faceted querying as nodes and edges are typed.",
    "One cost of hybrid graphs is that they require substantially more storage space than simple graphs.",
    "The third approach results in a complex graph, such as KaBOB 7, often built on the Web Ontology Language (OWL; https://www.w3.org/TR/owl-features) (Fig. 2c).",
    "Complex graphs are more expressive, facilitating the generation of new knowledge via deductive inference 32."
  ],
